:16:49','2012-05-07 07:16:49','Service Design Concept for First Niagara Bank.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/Screen-shot-2011-05-14-at-4.49.32-PM_9002.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-487\" title=\"Screen shot 2011-05-14 at 4.49.32 PM_900\" src=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/Screen-shot-2011-05-14-at-4.49.32-PM_9002-650x361.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"650\" height=\"361\" /></a>\r\n\r\nFirst Niagara had a need to discover and retain Gen-Y customers. This project was focused on leveraging digital natives behavior and creative an experience that aligned with their motivations as they relate to banking.\r\n\r\nSo what\'s so special about this app? UberPay.me has a 2 step registration process. Gaining new customers via a simple text. Step one you receive a text that says something along the lines of\" Hey you just got paid $10, reply with a password to make an account\" Then you reply with a password and Boom. (step 2) You just signed up for a light-weight checking account via text. Really it\'s more like 1 step since all you have to do is reply with a password... Obviously you will need to fill in some more personal information like SS# etc. However in this concept we propose to spread the cumbersome registration process through \"unlocking\" phases to give more comfort to the user. This is on their time, when they want it, where they want it. That is Uberpay.me. The best way to send and receive money with a text or an email.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/Screen-shot-2011-05-14-at-4.52.09-PM_9001.png\"><img title=\"Screen shot 2011-05-14 at 4.52.09 PM_900\" src=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/Screen-shot-2011-05-14-at-4.52.09-PM_9001-650x365.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"650\" height=\"365\" /></a>\r\n\r\nIn the future when the user reaches the account fund limit they are introduced to First Niagara\'s Savings accounts. Now that your Gen Y customer is comfortable with your App, they are now ready to get serious and commit a bit more. It\'s super easy now too because the bank already has all of their important information. Just click a button online to add a savings account and customers can start transferring money from their UberPay.me accounts instantly and free.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','UberPay.me, First Niagara Bank','','publish','open','open','','enter-title-here','','','2012-05-28 22:53:48','2012-05-29 02:53:48','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?post_type=project&#038;p=47',0,'project','',0),(48,1,'2012-05-07 07:17:01','2012-05-07 07:17:01','ok.','this is a new post.','','trash','open','open','','this-is-a-new-post','','','2012-05-07 07:22:13','2012-05-07 07:22:13','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?post_type=project&#038;p=48',0,'project','',0),(49,1,'2012-05-07 07:17:37','2012-05-07 07:17:37','<strong>Louis Vuitton, Case Study</strong>\r\n\r\nComprised of 4 Columbia Business School MBA\'s and 4 Parsons BFA\'s our brilliant team put together by the <a href=\"http://www.luxuryeducationfoundation.org/about-lef/119\">Luxury Education Foundation</a>, approached Louis Vuitton\'s design brief with a multifaceted perspective.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nLouise Vuitton 2011 Brief\r\n\r\nWith five Manhattan stores, New York City represents an important and growing market for Louis Vuitton. As the company plans renovations in all of its New York City locations, a team comprised of students from two of the city’s most prestigious institutions of learning, Columbia Business School (CBS) and Parsons The New School for Design, embarked on a case study to determine how best to differentiate the five New York stores, both amongst each other and within the competitive contexts of their respective local neighborhoods.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">[video type=\"vimeo\" clip_id=\"32983147\" title=\"Louis Vuitton \" width=\"600\" height=\"337\"]</p>\r\n“The Emotions of Travel”\r\n\r\nNo other luxury brand signifies the concepts of journey and travel as significantly as does Louis Vuitton. After extensive market research, the CBS and Parsons team learned that, for many, the most important – and memorable – aspect of any journey is the emotion that it invokes. As a customer journeys through one, or all, of the New York City’s Louis Vuitton stores, they will feel one or more of five distinctive emotions of travel – glamour, wonder, anticipation, escape, and romance – all of which are intrinsic to the Louis Vuitton brand. Tailored to local neighborhood, clientele and store layout, and embodied in all aspects of the store experience (including store spirit and personality, product assortment, store architecture, layout and design, customer experience and services, and organization and staffing), four of the five stores will invoke a distinctive emotion of travel: SoHo–romance, Bloomingdale’s–glamour, Macy’s–anticipation, Saks Fifth Avenue–wonder. The 3 three floors of the Louis Vuitton Maison on 5th Avenue will each invoke a separate, but linked, emotion: 1st floor and luggage floor–anticipation, 2nd floor (men’s)–escape, 3rd floor (women’s ready-to-wear)–glamour.','Louis Vuitton ','','publish','open','open','','i-just-need-one-more-post-after-this','','','2012-05-27 22:50:29','2012-05-28 02:50:29','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?post_type=project&#038;p=49',0,'project','',0),(50,1,'2012-05-07 07:18:04','2012-05-07 11:18:04','Thoroughly investigating residential buildings and their stakeholders in manhattan revealed some interesting findings. Our insights showed an immense disconnect of social contact and the lack of existing tools or methods to have a community. InHouse answers the many gaps we discovered within communication and exchange. By sharing goods, skills, and a building activity calendar it empowers tenants to build community and friendship!\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">[video type=\"vimeo\" clip_id=\"17484320\" title=\"inHouse, a platform for neighbors\" width=\"600\" height=\"337\"]</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">[portfolio_slideshow exclude=\"77\"]</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Hat tip to my creative partner Rachel Happ.</p>','inHouse, a platform for neighbors','','publish','closed','closed','','inhouse-platform-for-neighbors','','','2012-05-29 00:12:07','2012-05-29 04:12:07','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?post_type=project&#038;p=50',0,'project','',0),(51,1,'2012-05-29 00:09:14','2012-05-29 04:09:14','Thoroughly investigating residential buildings and their stakeholders in manhattan revealed some interesting findings. Our insights showed an immense disconnect of social contact and the lack of existing tools or methods to have a community. InHouse answers the many gaps we discovered within communication and exchange. By sharing goods, skills, and a building activity calendar it empowers tenants to build community and friendship!\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">[video type=\"vimeo\" clip_id=\"17484320\" title=\"inHouse, a platform for neighbors\" width=\"600\" height=\"337\"]</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">[portfolio_slideshow exclude=\"77\"]</p>','inHouse, a platform for neighbors','','inherit','open','open','','50-autosave','','','2012-05-29 00:09:14','2012-05-29 04:09:14','',50,'http://localhost:8080/?p=51',0,'revision','',0),(52,1,'2012-05-07 05:28:26','2012-05-07 05:28:26','[recent_work num=3]','Recent Work','','inherit','open','open','','12-revision-14','','','2012-05-07 05:28:26','2012-05-07 05:28:26','',12,'http://localhost:8080/?p=52',0,'revision','',0),(53,1,'2012-05-07 07:59:47','2012-05-07 07:59:47','Design Breif 2009\r\n<blockquote>Memorial Sloan Kettering’s Innovation Lab requested to create the site and service design for a new satellite chemotherapy site in Brooklyn. The design was to be based specifically on a thoughtful consideration of patients’ experience.</blockquote>\r\nAs of 2010 the Life Essentials kit and details from it have been brought to life and are in use at the <a href=\"http://www.mskcc.org/cancer-care/outpatient/brooklyn-infusion\" target=\"_blank\">Memorial Sloan Kettering Brooklyn Infusion Center</a>.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/front.jpeg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-522\" title=\"front\" src=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/front.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"588\" height=\"392\" /></a>\r\n\r\nLife Essentials, a welcoming kit:\r\nThe kit presented to Memorial Sloan Kettering was created to allow new chemo patients to feel more at home, relaxed, and like honored guests.\r\n\r\n<em>The kit includes: A personalized hand written welcome letter, herbal tea samples, aroma therapy oil samples, a healthy snack, an eye mask, a journal with mood and weather note sections. In addition the most important part is My Preferences which is a checklist and service that allows the patient to customize their visits - everything from favorite music, to the type of tea they would like and at what part of the day. This is a bespoke welcome service with every day essentials to make the chemo therapy experience as stress free as possible. </em>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/Screen-Shot-2011-12-07-at-9.25.08-PM_900.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-592\" title=\"Screen Shot 2011-12-07 at 9.25.08 PM_900\" src=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/Screen-Shot-2011-12-07-at-9.25.08-PM_900-565x650.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"565\" height=\"650\" /></a>\r\n\r\n[portfolio_slideshow exclude=\"10, 11, 12\"]\r\n\r\n<img title=\"gallery\" src=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wp-includes/js/tinymce/plugins/wpgallery/img/t.gif\" alt=\"\" />','Life Essentials, a welcoming kit.','','publish','open','open','','this-is-another-project','','','2012-05-30 21:35:02','2012-05-31 01:35:02','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?