’ve recently consulted with <strong>MTV </strong>and was a panelist invited by <strong>WHATIF</strong> for a study on Gen-Y trends. I have traveled the world extensively (my passport is almost full), I’m a pro at Where’s Waldo and I can be very competitive on the foose-ball table!\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div style=\"float: right; width: 35%; clear: right;\">\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">[toggle title=\"Education\"] [/toggle]</p>\r\n[twitter username=micahspear]','About','','inherit','open','open','','4-revision-54','','','2012-05-16 15:49:09','2012-05-16 19:49:09','',4,'http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=249',0,'revision','',0),(239,1,'2012-05-16 03:51:26','2012-05-16 03:51:26','<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-229\" title=\"hoeweler_micah_final21-731x1024\" src=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/hoeweler_micah_final21-731x1024-214x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"214\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nPlayfulness and improvisation are vital organs in the body of my design process. I love producing winning products. Some of the most remarkable inventions were created by accident which excites me to experiment. I intend on bringing design and technology closer – thoughtfully – and with consideration for our needs and desires.  Thanks to Art School, Design School, and Business School where I focused on Service Design and Environmental Studies. I’ve experimented with different strategies of identifying and realizing scalable and high impact products in teams of all types. Recently I’ve consulted for <strong>Louis Vuitton</strong> on luxury marketing strategy, service design and Store differentiation, <strong>Memorial Sloan Kettering</strong> on Health Service Innovation for chemo therapy patients, <strong>First Niagara Bank</strong> on Gen-Y strategy, and was recently on an <strong>MTV </strong>event panel contracted by <strong>WHATIF</strong> for a study on Gen-Y trends. I grew up in the countr