1024-214x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"214\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nPlayfulness and improvisation are vital organs in the body of my design process. I love creating winning products, and because some of the most remarkable inventions were an accident, it excites me to experiment with my ideas. I grew up in the countryside where I climbed trees and played in the woods. From a young age I was blowing glass, painting canvases, shooting travel photography, and making things. I’ve put these passions to work at Art School, Design School, and Business School where I focused on Service Design and Environmental Studies. I’ve experimented with different strategies of identifying and realizing scalable and high impact products on my own and in teams working closely with others. I’ve consulted for <strong>Louis Vuitton</strong> on luxury marketing strategy and service design, <strong>Memorial Sloan Kettering</strong> on Health Service Innovation for chemotherapy patients and <strong>First Niagara Bank</strong> on Gen-Y strategy. I’ve recently consulted with <strong>MTV </strong>and was a panelist invited by <strong>WHATIF</strong> for a study on Gen-Y trends. I have traveled the world extensively (my passport is almost full), I’m a pro at Where’s Waldo and I can be very competitive on the foose-ball table!\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Education: Maryland Institute College of Art, Yestermerrow Design Build School, Eugene Lang the New School for Liberal Arts, Parsons the New School for Design, Columbia Business School</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><a href=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?attachment_id=305\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-305\"><img src=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/twitter_icon.png\" alt=\"\" title=\"twitter_icon\" width=\"32\" height=\"22\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-305\" /></a>[twitter username=micahspear]</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div></div>\r\n&nbsp;','About','','inherit','open','open','','4-revision-72','','','2